</taxonomicName>
can be characterized, among other characters, by the straight hind margin of penis, genital sclerites sclerotized and discernible, and styliger plate projected, covering entirely the penis (adapted from 
<bibRefCitation id="AF1D4B3BFFC7FFC8FF06B7A4FDDDB7EE" author="Alba-Tercedor, J. &amp; Mosquera, S." box="[151,529,223,249]" pageId="8" pageNumber="118" pagination="61 - 67" refId="ref6918" refString="Alba-Tercedor, J. &amp; Mosquera, S. (1999) Caenis chamie, a new species from Colombia (Ephemeroptera: Caenidae). Pan- Pacific Entomologist, 75 (2), 61 - 67." type="journal article" year="1999">Alba-Tercedor &amp; Mosquera 1999</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
